Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.mailbox

Enum MailboxAttribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MailboxAttribute>
      • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.mailbox.MailboxAttribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MailboxAttribute>
    public enum MailboxAttribute
extends java.lang.Enum<MailboxAttribute>
    Enumeration of IMAP mailbox attributes.

    These attributes are defined in RFC 9051 (IMAP4rev2) Section 7.2.2 and RFC 6154 (Special-Use Mailboxes).

    Author:
    Chris Burdess
    See Also:
    RFC 9051 Section 7.2.2, RFC 6154 Special-Use Mailboxes

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      ALL
      Virtual mailbox containing all messages.
      ARCHIVE
      Used for archive messages.
      DRAFTS
      Used for draft messages.
      FLAGGED
      Virtual mailbox containing all flagged messages.
      HASCHILDREN
      The mailbox has child mailboxes that are accessible.
      HASNOCHILDREN
      The mailbox has no child mailboxes that are accessible.
      IMPORTANT
      Used for important messages.
      JUNK
      Used for junk/spam messages.
      MARKED
      The mailbox has been marked "interesting" by the server.
      NOINFERIORS
      Mailbox cannot have any child mailboxes.
      NONEXISTENT
      The mailbox does not actually exist, but is a placeholder for child mailboxes.
      NOSELECT
      Not a real mailbox; just a placeholder in the hierarchy.
      REMOTE
      The mailbox exists on a remote server.
      SENT
      Used for sent messages.
      SUBSCRIBED
      The mailbox is subscribed.
      TRASH
      Used for deleted/trash messages.
      UNMARKED
      The mailbox does not contain any additional messages since the last time it was selected.
